Eczacibasi Yapi, Ericom, Turkcell: Turkey Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-06-09T06:32:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/eczacibasi-yapi-ericom-turkcell-turkey-equity-market-preview.html
The following stocks may be active in
 Turkey . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from the last
close.  Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100 index (XU100)  fell 396.12, or
0.6 percent, to 64,067.11 yesterday.  Eczacibasi Yapi Gerecleri Sanayi & Ticaret AS (ECYAP TI):
The Turkish maker of ceramic sanitary ware, fittings and
bathroom furniture will increase its investment in  Russia  to
more than 50 million euros ($73 million) by setting up a second
tile plant, new stores and storages, Vatan reported. The
company’s first, 35 million-euros Russian plant started
operations two weeks ago, the Istanbul-based newspaper said,
citing Husamettin Onanc, head of the building products group in
parent company Eczacibasi Holding. Eczacibasi Yapi dropped 2
kurus, or 0.7 percent, to 3.04 liras.  Ericom Telekomunikasyon & Enerji Teknolojileri AS (ERICO
TI): The Turkish supplier of energy storage systems for
communications services will start trading on the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange  at a reference price of 3.55 liras today, the bourse
said. Ericom sold 2.25 million shares, or a 41 percent stake in
an initial public offering on June 3.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL TI): Turkey’s
antitrust regulator will announce a decision on whether the
country’s biggest mobile-phone operator unlawfully restricted
competition in distribution and retail sales. Turkcell was
unchanged at 8.9 liras.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
